Ōmura, Nagasaki.label: Ōmura
Ōmura, Nagasaki.description:
Ōmura is a city located in Nagasaki Prefecture, Japan.
As of January 1, 2009, the city has an estimated population of 89,891 and a population density of 710 persons per km². The total area is 126.33 km², and includes Nagasaki Airport. Wikipedia

Ōnojō, Fukuoka.description: Ōnojō is an area located in Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan. Its name is made up of the kanji for 'big', 'field', and 'castle'. It is mostly a southern suburb of the city of Fukuoka, and has a border to the northwest with the Hakata-ku area of the city. Wikipedia

Šiauliai.label: Šiauliai
